finally git was working through the debian distribution of ubuntu.

The steps are as follows;

Sudo apt-get install git

git remote add origin <remote url>

this remote url is the url of the repository in the git domain.

Attempt pulling the git repository will sync any of the git materials available there

pushing the git repository will sync

git commit will save the changes locally

git status provides the details of the status

git init will initially initializes and seed the git repo in the mentioned folder

git pull will pull all the code in the existing libraries. 
  

